16
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:10,800
little bit more care, and with a little bit more attention to the kind of principles that

17
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:15,840
I wanted to emphasize with the whole event. The downside, which is not to be taken lightly,

18
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:21,360
is that it gives the false impression that success looks like winning, but it does not.

19
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:25,920
Success means having more material out there that explains math and inspires people to engage with

20
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:30,400
it. Ten years from now, no one is going to remember my arbitrary selections, but every

21
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:34,560
one of the pieces made will still exist and will still potentially help someone trying to learn.

22
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:40,320
